en","1230–Female":"1230–Overleden","1270–Male":"1270–Overleden","1284–Male":"1284–Overleden","1196–Male":"1196–Overleden","1198–Female":"1198–Overleden","Abt 1285":"circa 1285","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1230":"1230","ABT    1270":"circa 1270","1196":"1196","1284":"1284","1270":"1270","1218":"1218","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","of Llechryd,Diserth and Tre-,Radnorshire,Wales":"Disserth, Radnorshire, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1230–":"1230–Deceased","1218–Male":"1218–Deceased","1220–Male":"1220–Deceased","1230–Male":"1230–Deceased","1230–Female":"1230–Deceased","1270–Male":"1270–Deceased","1284–Male":"1284–Deceased","1196–Male":"1196–Deceased","1198–Female":"1198–Deceased","Abt 1285":"about 1285","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1230":"1230","ABT    1270":"about 1270","1196":"1196","1284":"1284","1270":"1270","1218":"1218","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","of Llechryd,Diserth and Tre-,Radnorshire,Wales":"Disserth, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"ap","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Geza, Jeno, Arpad, Attila, Csaba.","Hungarian: variant of   Papp  , meaning ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’. This surname is also found in Romania, Slovakia, Croatia, and Serbia, and also among Rusyns (in Serbia and Croatia). See also   Pop   2 and   Popa  .","English: variant of   Pape   1."],"variants":[{"name":"Papp","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Hungarian Laszlo, Zoltan, Geza, Istvan, Gabor, Miklos, Tibor, Arpad, Denes, Imre, Attila.","German (Bavaria, Tyrol): from Middle High German <i>pap</i> ‘baby food’, Dutch <i>pap</i> ‘porridge, pap’, hence perhaps a nickname denoting someone who had lost his teeth or subsisted on a meager diet.","Hungarian: from <i>pap</i> ‘priest (of the Catholic or Orthodox Church)’, probably an occupational name for someone in the service of a priest or a nickname for a pious person. This surname is also found in Romania and Slovakia, and also among Rusyns. Compare   Pap   and   Pop  ."]}]},{"name":"Hywel","type":"LAST","meanings":["A Welsh name. Some write the name Hoel, which they render 'lordly;' if so, it may come from huail, a vice-regent, regent. Arthur derives the surname Howell from Corn. -Brit, houl, the sun; and he adds, high, exalted.' But Hywel is rather from hywel, conspicuous."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Leuan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Iohannes</i>.  See  <b>John</b>   ."],"variants":[{"name":"Iefan","meanings":["Later form of   Ieuan ."]},{"name":"Ifan","meanings":["From Latin <i>Iohannes</i>.  See  <b>John</b>   ."]},{"name":"John","meanings":["Contracted form of Old French <i>Jo(h)anne</i>, from Latin <i>Io(h)anna</i> (  see  Joanna  ). In England this was the usual feminine form of   John   from the Middle English period onwards and was extremely popular, but in the 16th and 17th centuries it steadily lost ground to   Jane .  It was strongly revived in the first part of the 20th century, partly under the influence of  George Bernard Shaw's  play St Joan (  1923 ), based on the life of  Joan of Arc  (  1412–31 ). Claiming to be guided by the voices of the saints, she persuaded the French dauphin to defy the occupying English forces and have himself crowned, and she led the French army that raised the siege of Orleans in  1429 . The following year she was captured by the Burgundians and sold to the English, and a year later she was burned at the stake for witchcraft at the age of 18 or 19. Her story has captured the imagination of many writers, and she is variously portrayed as a national and political hero, a model of apolitical straightforwardness and honesty, and a religious heroine. She was canonized in  1920 . More recent influences have included the American film actress  Joan Crawford  (  1908–77 , born  Lucille le Sueur ), the British actress  Joan Collins  (  b. 1933 ), the American comedienne  Joan Rivers  (  b. 1933 ), and the West Indian pop singer  Joan Armatrading  (  b. 1950 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Leuan ap Hywel was born in 1230, in Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Hywel ap Seissyl, was 34 and his mother, Gwenllian verch Maredudd, was 32. He married Gwladus verch Ieuan about 1285. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1230–":"1230–Surnud","1218–Male":"1218–Surnud","1220–Male":"1220–Surnud","1230–Male":"1230–Surnud","1230–Female":"1230–Surnud","1270–Male":"1270–Surnud","1284–Male":"1284–Surnud","1196–Male":"1196–Surnud","1198–Female":"1198–Surnud","Abt 1285":"umbes 1285","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1230":"1230","ABT    1270":"umbes 1270","1196":"1196","1284":"1284","1270":"1270","1218":"1218","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","of Llechryd,Diserth and Tre-,Radnorshire,Wales":"Disserth, Radnorshire, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1230–":"1230–Kuollut","1218–Male":"1218–Kuollut","1220–Male":"1220–Kuollut","1230–Male":"1230–Kuollut","1230–Female":"1230–Kuollut","1270–Male":"1270–Kuollut","1284–Male":"1284–Kuollut","1196–Male":"1196–Kuollut","1198–Female":"1198–Kuollut","Abt 1285":"noin 1285","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1230":"1230","ABT    1270":"noin 1270","1196":"1196","1284":"1284","1270":"1270","1218":"1218","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","of Llechryd,Diserth and Tre-,Radnorshire,Wales":"Disserth, Radnorshire, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1230–":"1230–Décédé","1218–Male":"1218–Décédé","1220–Male":"1220–Décédé","1230–Male":"1230–Décédé","1230–Female":"1230–Décédée","1270–Male":"1270–Décédé","1284–Male":"1284–Décédé","1196–Male":"1196–Décédé","1198–Female":"1198–Décédée","Abt 1285":"environ 1285","1198":"1198","1220":"1220","1230":"1230","ABT    1270":"environ 1270","1196":"1196","1284":"1284","1270":"1270","1218":"1218","Wales, United Kingdom":"Pays de Gall